[tool-call] delta {"path":"tests/src/commons-httpclient/commons-httpclient/3.0/src/test/java/commons_httpclient/commons_httpclient/ReflectionSocketFactoryTest.java","edits":[{"oldText":"public class ReflectionSocketFactoryTest {\n    @Test\n    @Order(1)\n    void translatesReflectedSocketTimeoutException() throws Exception {","newText":"public class ReflectionSocketFactoryTest {\n    @Test\n    @Order(1)\n    void createsSocketWithPublicFactoryClassName() throws Exception {\n        Socket socket = ReflectionSocketFactory.createSocket(RecordingSocketFactory.class.getName(), \"127.0.0.1\", 80,\n                InetAddress.getLoopbackAddress(), 0, 250);\n        if (socket == null) {\n            return;\n        }\n        try (Socket ignored = socket) {\n            assertThat(socket).isInstanceOf(RecordingSocket.class);\n            RecordingSocket recordingSocket = (RecordingSocket) socket;\n            assertThat(recordingSocket.bound).isTrue();\n            assertThat(recordingSocket.connected).isTrue();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(2)\n    void translatesReflectedSocketTimeoutException() throws Exception {"},{"oldText":"    @Order(2)\n    @Test\n    void createsBoundSocketWithJdkSocketFactory() throws Exception {","newText":"    @Order(3)\n    @Test\n    void createsBoundSocketWithJdkSocketFactory() throws Exception {"},{"oldText":"    public static final class TimeoutSocketFactory {\n        public static TimeoutSocketFactory getDefault() {\n            return new TimeoutSocketFactory();\n        }\n\n        public Socket createSocket() {\n            return new TimeoutSocket();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class TimeoutSocket extends Socket {","newText":"    public static final class RecordingSocketFactory {\n        public static RecordingSocketFactory getDefault() {\n            return new RecordingSocketFactory();\n        }\n\n        public Socket createSocket() {\n            return new RecordingSocket();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class TimeoutSocketFactory {\n        public static TimeoutSocketFactory getDefault() {\n            return new TimeoutSocketFactory();\n        }\n\n        public Socket createSocket() {\n            return new TimeoutSocket();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingSocket extends Socket {\n        private boolean bound;\n        private boolean connected;\n\n        @Override\n        public void bind(SocketAddress bindpoint) {\n            bound = true;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void connect(SocketAddress endpoint, int timeout) {\n            connected = true;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class TimeoutSocket extends Socket {"}]}
[tool-call] end id=call_5H6Q4CUfEw4KRpoZ7FUHAK1R|fc_0ccf52965e5b6820016a04623bffa88193bc73cb96bb4650da name=edit args={"path": "tests/src/commons-httpclient/commons-httpclient/3.0/src/test/java/commons_httpclient/commons_httpclient/ReflectionSocketFactoryTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "public class ReflectionSocketFactoryTest {\n    @Test\n    @Order(1)\n    void translatesReflectedSocketTimeoutException() throws Exception {", "newText": "public class ReflectionSocketFactoryTest {\n    @Test\n    @Order(1)\n    void createsSocketWithPublicFactoryClassName() throws Exception {\n        Socket socket = ReflectionSocketFactory.createSocket(RecordingSocketFactory.class.getName(), \"127.0.0.1\", 80,\n                InetAddress.getLoopbackAddress(), 0, 250);\n        if (socket == null) {\n            return;\n        }\n        try (Socket ignored = socket) {\n            assertThat(socket).isInstanceOf(RecordingSocket.class);\n            RecordingSocket recordingSocket = (RecordingSocket) socket;\n            assertThat(recordingSocket.bound).isTrue();\n            assertThat(recordingSocket.connected).isTrue();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(2)\n    void translatesReflectedSocketTimeoutException() throws Exception {"}, {"oldText": "    @Order(2)\n    @Test\n    void createsBoundSocketWithJdkSocketFactory() throws Exception {", "newText": "    @Order(3)\n    @Test\n    void createsBoundSocketWithJdkSocketFactory() throws Exception {"}, {"oldText": "    public static final class TimeoutSocketFactory {\n        public static TimeoutSocketFactory getDefault() {\n            return new TimeoutSocketFactory();\n        }\n\n        public Socket createSocket() {\n            return new TimeoutSocket();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class TimeoutSocket extends Socket {", "newText": "    public static final class RecordingSocketFactory {\n        public static RecordingSocketFactory getDefault() {\n            return new RecordingSocketFactory();\n        }\n\n        public Socket createSocket() {\n            return new RecordingSocket();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class TimeoutSocketFactory {\n        public static TimeoutSocketFactory getDefault() {\n            return new TimeoutSocketFactory();\n        }\n\n        public Socket createSocket() {\n            return new TimeoutSocket();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingSocket extends Socket {\n        private boolean bound;\n        private boolean connected;\n\n        @Override\n        public void bind(SocketAddress bindpoint) {\n            bound = true;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void connect(SocketAddress endpoint, int timeout) {\n            connected = true;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class TimeoutSocket extends Socket {"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering factory test implementation**\n\nI'm thinking about adding a second custom factory success test before the timeout. This would help exercise the generated class without needing a network. It involves using the `bind` and `connect` methods reflectively, but I'm not sure if it fully covers line 50. However, it doesn't seem to hurt to add it, as it might increase coverage. I believe it will be in the same file, so it could be beneficial overall.\n\n**Clarifying class naming rules**\n\nI’m exploring the rules around test class naming. Top-level test classes can indeed be public, and inner classes can be public static. It seems that class names don't necessarily see direct correlation to their file names. I shouldn't use `$` in test class or file names because they produce `$` in bytecode, but this doesn't apply to inner class names in source. I think I’m ready to implement these guidelines!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ccf52965e5b6820016a0461fac59481939e424dee7e8bf857\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqBGI8TGDsE74OkAprPMA8Rv5JZkTqjqKSorLUDb2cHOFJM4c_7hkikX3OLC0_CA0i1BjeGwzZAXx-67qMhWcgR90i40q-8ij0vbST6QdLQQcoRYenaE8ikFu7ZKiaie0B07u9KyTlKfB3uiMHQ68vg1mIOB8DRnhSvBfrx5b4IAFCrt_bPLcliQFxChHhzNToQ6zQnoYUKocSCNV8w-B9rpWEzmNG94-T0J955CIPLBDqjbi6ASX7_DbCKBdYcvUCkz3IUl3GiEALU-BYdnWAxiDfc-DWhCQdRuI7CiCdu_D4il59_ys233anAvmFRTuDOp-jQlMp1bu_a_vIja53uO2SkFlffiwVZgYtmZleN1V2Vwpw0n82pMVUBk7uqQ403yUx-a1-lOsA1DZEs-cLAcoEVpHaD3Glp2erFJugCSBceyuXbsyZ9mKZ7SQDkLp7UPGApGAXbwVLO_kVVX-hwbE876nsYTiogq9S_23gdj5CbhyyduBRCSrVDMnrFHqDnLAPGQn7bp16G2K8whu5Z4bej8t7yKDpsGfYh_HC41erBgBkmy9MU80qMxHwuzcD1UvpRJfYyh0vVQyijQuFLppEk5gI2WjT5kuoXKEJ7ZETICr_4dxVaesAbeN0lBqbIM1VIiSwUz3OEcIKfnYVqeXdPrybqwJoVaBrl2HzbFsX_CARrlWeCz-HzjhHZwQc_6ADTGbnfQugCOXmEbAdcwebxQWxr4xvfeasIU2MZKt09-ehAicB1mfNnWLKAbbMmbquQf5_jg1e8dKJGsji-Qi3RtMv4pu9BVYxuD2gm2If0YGEmS-1W4_rZsHx6ZH